extends base

block content
    .container

        h2 Dependencies

        p Install ZeroMQ, Node.js and npm

        pre
            | $ sudo apt-get install nodejs npm libzmq-dev
            | $ sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node # To fix node-gyp on Ubuntu

        h2 Install Somata

        p Install Somata from <a href='https://npmjs.org'>npm</a>:

        pre
            | $ npm install somata

        h2 Somata Registry

        p Install the Somata Registry globally:

        pre
            | $ npm install -g somata-registry

        p Start the registry:

        pre
            | $ somata-registry

        p Now when you start a Somata Service it will register with the Registry and be accessible from the rest of your codebase.

        p Try <a href='/examples'>some simple examples</a> to continue.
